  "title": "Project Engineer (Civil)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<p>a) To report to the Manager or team leader as shown in the organization chart. He/she is responsible for the assigned or related project tasks and responsibilities.</p>\n<p>b) The detailed duties and responsibilities include but not limited to the following:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Study and fully understand the ISO requirements, technical drawings, scope, contractual requirements and sub-contract agreements. Work with the consultants to resolve technical issues prior to construction.</li>\n  <li>Submit to superior for feedback and concurrence on short or medium-term programmes and execute the works according to the detailed programme.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that the works are carried out according to the approved drawings, quality procedures and EHS requirements. Managing the works with excellent housekeeping is a key focus.</li>\n  <li>For quality management, the engineer is responsible to fully implement with the quality recordings, carry out result analysis and formulate action plans for continuous improvement.</li>\n  <li>Implement and maintain proper recordings to comply with EHS, quality, client and authorities’ requirements.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for cost management so that the materials used for both temporary works and permanent works are not damaged or control the wastage within specified tolerance. Rework or abortive work which has serious time and cost impacts shall be avoided.</li>\n  <li>Ad-hoc matters as assigned by the PM which is necessary for the execution of the project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Bachelor's degree in Civil &amp; Structural Engineering</li>\n  <li>Mininum 2 - 5 years' experience working in construction industry</li>\n  <li>Preferably with HDB experience</li>\n</ul>",
